            <p><h3>Is all documentation used in the bidding contests of concession or PPP projects available on the GViP Brazil platform?</h3></p>
            <p>No. The platform is a tool for the dissemination of Brazilian projects. The bidding contest documents considered with legal value are published only on pages with the domain ".gov.br". The GViP Brazil platform contains links to access these documents.</p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            <p><h3>What are the main Brazilian laws regulating the bidding process of the concession and PPP sectors?</h3></p>
            <p>The main law that establishes the bidding rules in Brazil is No. 8666/1993. For the concessions sector, the main laws are Nos. 8987/1995 and 9074/1995. For the PPP sector, the main law is No. 11.079 / 2004. The Brazilian Investment Partnership Program (PPI), which coordinates the Federal Projects, is established by law No. 13,334/2016. All laws can be accessed through the page at <a href="http://www.planalto.gov.br/ccivil_03/">http://www.planalto.gov.br/ccivil_03/</a>.</p>
            <p>&nbsp;</p>
            <p><h3>What are the main government agencies involved in the planning process and the structuring of concession and PPP projects in the Brazilian Federal Government?</h3></p>
            <p>Government policies are set by central ministries (the Presidency of the Republic, the Ministry of Finance and the Ministry of Planning, Development and Management) in conjunction with sectoral ministries for each sector, such as the Ministry of Transport, Ports and Civil Aviation and the Ministry of Mines and Energy.</p>
            <p>The sectoral regulation and management of concession and PPP contracts are carried out by the sectoral regulatory agencies such as the National Civil Aviation Agency (ANAC) for the operation and air infrastructure sector.</p>

